
##  Prompt Engineering Reference — WilliamsF1 Audit Project (CRAFT Aligned)

This section documents all critical prompt engineering instructions used (and recommended) for building, testing, and maintaining the **WilliamsF1 Workstation Audit Framework**.

---

###  Prompts Already Used Correctly

| Layer | Prompt | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|
| **C – Clear Command**       | `Give me a full PowerShell script with admin check, error logging, and file export to CSV and HTML`   | Ensures clear entry-point and output audit trail |
| **R – Robust Reasoning**    | `Explain why we use \`$policy -eq 'Restricted'\` and exit codes` | Validates script logic reasoning   |
| **A – Automation Friendly** | `Wrap this script in a Makefile.ps1 and call it with a single task` | Automation entry-point creation |
| **F – Failsafe Design**     | `Confirm this script makes no destructive changes and only audits` | Ensures safe read-only posture   |
| **T – Testable Templates**  | `Split this into modular structure under /lib/, /requirements/, /scripts/`                            | Reusability and version control compliance |

